required: java 17

step 1:- sudo apt update

step 2:- sudo apt upgrade -y

step 3:- java -version

java version should be 17.

step 4:- curl -fsSL https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key | sudo tee /usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc > /dev/null

step 5:- echo "deb [signed-by=/usr/share/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc] https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/" | sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null

step 6:- sudo apt update

            sudo apt install jenkins -y

step 7:-  sudo systemctl start jenkins

                sudo systemctl enable jenkins

step 8:- go to website  http://localhost:8080

for password use step 9

step 9:- sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword

step 10:- Install plugins

Choose: Install suggested plugins

Wait for installation to complete.

step 11:- Create admin user
  Fill in:
Username

Password

Full Name

Email

step 12:- Jenkins is Ready
            Click “Start using Jenkins”.
